        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 12:01AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
line of strong thunderstorms along a line extending from Myricks Mill
to Jeffersonville, and moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, the leading
edge of this line of storms has also exhibited areas of
localized rotation. A brief tornado could quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Jeffersonville, Irwinton, McIntyre, Fitzpatrick, Myricks Mill, and
Ripley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
